723080f-a.text:
Rutgers Street, at the N.W. corner of Henry Street, showing the St. Teresa's R.C. Church. On the left is Henry Street, north side, west of Rutgers Street. Construction work in the foreground, is at the N.E. corner.
April 20. 1931.
P. L. Sperr.

720370f-a.text:
Henry Street, east from Rutgers Street, showing clearance at the N.E. corner, after demolition of the 6-story corner house No. 149-153. Also shown is the School for Crippled Children No. 155-159.(adjoining the clearance). In the far background is visible a portion of the Williamsburg
Bridge.
April 15, 1932.
P. L. Sperr.
